quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  29,53,"They ask you to hasten the punishment. If it were not for a stipulated term, the punishment would have come to them already. It will come upon them suddenly when they are not expecting it"
  29,54,They ask you to hasten the punishment but Hell already encircles the kafirun
  29,55,"On the Day the punishment envelops them from above them and from underneath their feet, He will say, ´Taste what you were doing!´"
  29,56,"My slaves, you who have iman, My earth is wide, so worship Me alone"
  29,57,Every self will taste death. Then you will be returned to Us
  29,58,"As for those who have iman and do right actions, We will lodge them in lofty chambers in the Garden, with rivers flowing under them, remaining in them timelessly, for ever. How excellent is the reward of those who act"
  29,59,those who are steadfast and put their trust in their Lord
  29,60,"How many creatures do not carry their provision with them! Allah provides for them and He will for you. He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them, ´Who created the heavens and the earth and made the sun and moon subservient?´ they will say, ´Allah.´ So how have they been perverted"
  29,62,Allah expands the provision of any of His slaves He wills and restricts it. Allah has knowledge of all things
  29,63,"If you ask them, ´Who sends down water from the sky, bringing the earth back to life again after it was dead?´ they will say, ´Allah.´ Say: ´Praise be to Allah.´ But most of them do not use their intellect"